gomodel:SYNGO_1178  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In figure 5 the authors use cortical neurone generated from their intersection null mice. The neurone are transfected with synaptophlourin (SynpHlourin) and stimulated electrophysiologically to cause exocytosis of the SVs and enhanced SynpHlourin fluorescence. With termination of the stimulus, SV are reformed by endocytosis, causing quenching of the pHlourin signal and this is delayed in KO cultures.. Experimental description: From the abstract, \"..we generated Itsn1 null mice\"." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
